1
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,760
<i>Help. Help.</i>

2
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:21,240
<i>I've been kidnapped. Is anyone around?</i>

3
00:03:21,760 --> 00:03:26,000
<i>Help. Help. I've been kidnapped.</i>

4
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,520
Mr. Warat.

5
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:23,160
You want me to
edit Mr. Sin's documents, right?

6
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,240
Make both his and mine
look as seamless as possible.

7
00:04:26,840 --> 00:04:28,440
Got it, easy.

8
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:40,800
Oh, Ms. Kluay. Som.

9
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:43,640
- Hm?
- Your sister.

10
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,720
Kluay.

11
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,040
Where are you going?

12
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,880
I saw a sign.

13
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,400
What sign?

14
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,400
Mr. Warat has been kidnapped.

15
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:56,600
Where?

16
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,520
I don't know.

17
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:00,960
Then where are you going to look?

18
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:03,560
I heard his voice…

19
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:06,080
<i>Help. I'm stuck here.</i>

20
00:05:06,840 --> 00:05:09,520
<i>Help. I'm stuck here.</i>

21
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:13,480
<i>Help. I'm stuck here.</i>

22
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:16,760
It's Mr. Warat's voice. But I know

23
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,240
that's not really him.

24
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:23,160
But it's late now. It's dangerous.
Don't go now.

25
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,960
- But…
- Let's go tomorrow.

26
00:05:27,880 --> 00:05:29,200
I can't wait.

27
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:34,040
Then we all go together.

28
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:51,160
They really came out.

29
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,080
Aunt Anong was right.

30
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,040
<i>What do I do now?</i>

31
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:57,680
Follow them carefully.
Don't let them notice you.

32
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,640
<i>I'm here, over here.</i>

33
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,280
This way.

34
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,240
This looks like
the building from my dream.

35
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,440
Really?

36
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,280
This place?

37
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Mr. Warat must be inside.

38
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:46,520
Mr. Warat?
Coming to a place like this at night?

39
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,680
<i>Kluay, I'm here.</i>

40
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:54,120
<i>Come help me. I'm stuck here.</i>

41
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:57,400
<i>I'm upstairs. Up here, Kluay.</i>

42
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:02,040
Something's off. Let's go in.

43
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:13,200
How is it, Mr. Sin? All set?

44
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,880
Mrs. Wanee has already announced the will.

45
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,200
You're incredible.

46
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,440
What about your side?

47
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,720
All taken care of.

48
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,520
We'll pin the blame
on the accounting department.

49
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,840
And Kluay?

50
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:24,720
She's already walked into the trap.

51
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:28,480
Too bad. I wanted to deal with her myself.
Whatever.

52
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:46,800
I'm scared, Arnon.

53
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:56,120
<i>I'm here, Kluay. I'm here.</i>

54
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:59,680
<i>I'm here, Kluay. I'm here. Up here.</i>

55
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,280
<i>Up here, Kluay.</i>

56
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:04,160
He says he's upstairs.

57
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,640
Who's there?

58
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,040
Come out now.

59
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:23,040
What? You're only tough around women?

60
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:29,800
Mr. Warat.

61
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,000
Mr. Warat.

62
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,480
Mr. Warat.

63
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:36,400
Where are you?

64
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,559
<i>I'm here, Kluay.</i>

65
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:43,320
Mr. Warat!

66
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:45,520
Som, go check on Ms. Kluay upstairs.

67
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:50,760
Where are you?

68
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:51,840
<i>Right here.</i>

69
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,560
Mr. Warat.

70
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:58,400
I… I'm here now.

71
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:00,600
<i>- I'm here.</i>
- I'm here.

72
00:09:01,680 --> 00:09:02,600
<i>I'm here.</i>

73
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,120
Kluay.

74
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:23,200
Kluay, where are you? Can you hear me?

75
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,600
Kluay.

76
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:27,800
Let's go back.

77
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:29,560
Mr. Warat's not here. Let's go.

78
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:32,440
He is. He's here.

79
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:36,840
Kluay!

80
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,240
Kluay.

81
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,600
Kluay!

82
00:09:47,720 --> 00:09:48,560
Som.

83
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:50,680
You're back.

84
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:54,280
What happened to me?

85
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,440
Kluay. Kluay.

86
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,240
- Kluay.
- Ms. Ampha?

87
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:26,960
Ms. Ampha. Ms. Ampha!

88
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:41,000
Kluay, I can't take this…

89
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,520
Kluay…

90
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:56,720
Kluay. Kluay.

91
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:11,160
Som.

92
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:15,080
Som. Som.

93
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:18,520
Som. Som.

94
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,240
Kluay.

95
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,840
Kluay. Kluay.

96
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,320
I'm here to help you, Kluay.

97
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:32,960
Mr. Warat, I…

98
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,840
I can't control myself.

99
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:41,800
Kluay, get yourself together.
You can do this. Trust me.

100
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:45,200
Kluay, I'm here.

101
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:48,360
Kluay, what's wrong? Kluay!

102
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:49,640
Let go of me.

103
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,880
Hey, Kluay!

104
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:53,200
Get out!

105
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:54,240
Kluay!

106
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:56,000
- Kluay.
- Let go of me.

107
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:59,360
Look at me. I know you can do this.

108
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:01,680
Get yourself together.

109
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,200
I'm not Kluay.

110
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:15,640
Ampha, why did you take my thing?!

111
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:19,160
Ampha!

112
00:12:22,520 --> 00:12:24,400
Kluay, come back.

113
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:27,320
I know that you can.

114
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:30,680
Listen to me. I love you.

115
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,840
Come back to me.

116
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:36,720
Kluay.

117
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,520
Kluay.

118
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:50,600
Kluay.

119
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,640
How did you end up at that building?

120
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,520
Ms. Ampha.

121
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,360
Ms. Ampha?

122
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,480
Yes.

123
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,200
I dreamed about it.

124
00:13:45,320 --> 00:13:47,440
- What's in that place?
<i>- Warat, help.</i>

125
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:48,920
Help? Help who?

126
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:51,200
<i>Someone evil is trying to take Kluay away.</i>

127
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,440
- Take her where?
<i>- You know it.</i>

128
00:13:53,520 --> 00:13:54,600
Where do I have to go?

129
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:58,360
And you went there?

130
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,520
Well,

131
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,880
Mr. Warat, can I ask you something?

132
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:08,000
Why did you suddenly leave
during the will announcement?

133
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:26,000
Everything we thought we knew

134
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:28,280
is all wrong.

135
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,600
What do you mean?

136
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,600
I'm Mr. Sarut's son.

137
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,600
How can you be sure?

138
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:44,120
I talked to him myself.

139
00:14:55,680 --> 00:14:56,800
So, what now?

140
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,960
He left me here

141
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:07,880
to live as part
of the Vanich family since I was a kid.

142
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:10,600
Look at what he did.

143
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,440
What about Mrs. Wanee?

144
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,080
She has known all along…

145
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:19,400
that I'm not my father's son.

146
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,960
So what are you going to do?

147
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,200
I don't know.

148
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,080
I think…

149
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,600
Where are you going?

150
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:44,920
Grandma's still awake.
I think I want to talk to her.

151
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:55,480
Mr. Warat, can I say something?

152
00:15:55,560 --> 00:15:57,320
I don't think it matters

153
00:15:57,400 --> 00:16:00,320
whether you're actually
from the Vanich bloodline.

154
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:03,080
How can it not matter?

155
00:16:03,680 --> 00:16:05,200
You already know what kind of person I am.

156
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:08,960
There's no way
I'll accept something that isn't mine.

157
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:11,720
So you're just going to
walk away from all of it?

158
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:15,160
No.

159
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:18,280
I'm not walking away like this.

160
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,120
Are you hurt?

161
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:32,040
No.

162
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:36,400
Thank you for…

163
00:16:39,520 --> 00:16:40,880
Mr. Warat.

164
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:45,000
Ms. Kluay was really worried about you.

165
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:05,440
Oh.

166
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:13,319
Well, why did you want
to name our daughter Waree?

167
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,440
I want her to be like water.

168
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,200
Water?

169
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:22,440
I want her life to be peaceful,

170
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:25,800
calm, and happy.

171
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:34,200
Waree Vanich, that's a beautiful name.

172
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:39,360
Thank you for being born, Waree.

173
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:07,000
Som.

174
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:11,080
Kluay, you're awake?

175
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:14,080
Last night…

176
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:16,640
I…

177
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:19,040
Kluay, it's me, Som.

178
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:20,720
Get yourself together, Kluay.

179
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,200
Last…

180
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,280
Last night, I…

181
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:27,680
- Kluay.
- Ah.

182
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,600
Just forget it.

183
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,800
Don't think about it anymore.

184
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:39,760
I'm sorry.

185
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:45,960
Where's Mr. Warat?

186
00:18:47,840 --> 00:18:49,040
Mr. Warat

187
00:18:50,040 --> 00:18:51,040
is back.

188
00:18:53,240 --> 00:18:54,520
Where is he now?

189
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:07,040
Mm.

190
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,800
Aunt Nong.

191
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:28,520
Why is it so dark?

192
00:19:31,640 --> 00:19:32,680
Aunt Nong?

193
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:35,320
Aunt Nong?

194
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:50,080
Aunt Nong!

195
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,280
Last night,

196
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,640
what were you doing out in the yard?

197
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:09,600
Well, last night,

198
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:11,880
I heard something,

199
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:15,840
a noise, so I went out to check.

200
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:20,880
I thought I was the only one who heard it.
You heard it too?

201
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:23,480
I checked already.

202
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:27,480
It was nothing. Probably the neighbors.

203
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:32,080
Then why did you end up sleeping outside?

204
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:34,560
I must be

205
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:38,320
getting old…
I must've fainted without realizing it.

206
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:42,680
Mom. Mom.

207
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:45,680
- Mom.
- Sin.

208
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:48,360
Mom. Mom.

209
00:20:49,480 --> 00:20:52,000
- Mom.
- I'm here, Sin.

210
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:54,400
I missed you so much.

211
00:20:58,480 --> 00:20:59,880
Don't worry.

212
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:02,880
I'll take good care of you.

213
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,360
I promise.

214
00:21:15,480 --> 00:21:17,480
No matter what happens,

215
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:21,160
I'll make sure everyone

216
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:23,320
who hurt us

217
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:28,120
pays for what belongs to you.

218
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:36,840
You can go to work.

219
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:39,200
I'm worried about you.

220
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:41,600
What about Uncle Rut?

221
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:45,840
He's at the hospital. Don't worry.

222
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:49,120
Just rest, he'll be back soon.

223
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,720
Today, Mrs. Wanee

224
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:57,240
is announcing the inheritance, right?

225
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,120
Yes.

226
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:04,800
You must have a lot to do.

227
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,640
Go to the office.

228
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:09,080
- Aunt Nong…
- Sin.

229
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:13,600
Go finish what we started.

230
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,320
You're back?

231
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:53,920
Grandma.

232
00:23:00,480 --> 00:23:01,960
I have something
I want to talk to you about.

233
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:04,320
Rat…

234
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:08,080
I want to apologize.

235
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,600
For what?

236
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,920
I talked to Mr. Sarut.

237
00:23:16,800 --> 00:23:18,400
Now I know

238
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:22,960
what really happened.

239
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,720
Rat.

240
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:37,160
Thank you so much

241
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,320
for raising me so well

242
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:44,320
- even though I…
- No, no.

243
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:48,880
What's done is done.

244
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:54,440
Your duty now
is to carry on the Vanich legacy.

245
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:56,560
And more importantly,

246
00:23:56,640 --> 00:24:00,600
you still have so many responsibilities
waiting for you.

247
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:04,600
Don't dwell on small things.

248
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:12,400
I can't, Mrs. Wanee.

249
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:17,440
Call me Grandma.

250
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:27,160
I don't know how to repay you, Grandma,

251
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,120
for raising me.

252
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:35,840
It's simple. Just repay me

253
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:39,800
by fulfilling the duty
you're supposed to do.

254
00:24:42,080 --> 00:24:45,560
No. We have to find Ms. Waree.

255
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:49,960
And how are you so sure she's still alive?

256
00:24:52,240 --> 00:24:53,520
I don't know

257
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:58,280
if she's alive or where she is.

258
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:02,480
But I promise I'll find her.

259
00:25:06,640 --> 00:25:09,720
Rat, listen to me.

260
00:25:10,920 --> 00:25:14,640
You don't have to go anywhere
or do anything more.

261
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:19,320
If it means losing you,

262
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:22,400
I don't want that.

263
00:25:57,320 --> 00:25:58,600
Hey.

264
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:00,160
I haven't seen you like this
in a long time.

265
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:04,600
What should I do?

266
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:06,640
Do nothing.

267
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:10,200
And if Ameena calls again,
don't answer. That's it.

268
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:12,680
But what if that's my kid?

269
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:18,640
If it is, then your kid's lucky
to be born into Warat's family.

270
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:21,080
That kid will live comfortably forever.

271
00:26:21,760 --> 00:26:24,600
You think life with me isn't enough?

272
00:26:24,680 --> 00:26:26,160
It is.

273
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:29,080
But with Warat, it'll be even better.

274
00:26:31,880 --> 00:26:35,880
But if it's really my kid,
do I really have to lose them?

275
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:39,520
Then start a new life.
The life you deserve.

276
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:42,160
- A new life?
- Det,

277
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:45,400
you've always liked Kluay, haven't you?

278
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:50,880
Let Ameena stay with Warat's family.

279
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:53,040
And you go be with Kluay. That's it.

280
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,560
- But that…
- Det,

281
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:59,200
opportunities like this don't come often.

282
00:27:10,120 --> 00:27:12,480
Who was that man last night?

283
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:14,320
Why was he following us?

284
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:19,400
And… what about Mr. Warat's voice?

285
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:25,040
That wasn't Mr. Warat's voice.

286
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:28,240
<i>Let's go back.</i>
<i>Mr. Warat's not here. Let's go.</i>

287
00:27:29,040 --> 00:27:30,760
<i>He is. He's here.</i>

288
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:32,160
Kluay.

289
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,520
Kluay!

290
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:41,320
From now on,

291
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:44,000
if you hear anything at night,

292
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:46,360
don't go anywhere.

293
00:27:53,240 --> 00:27:55,600
If I hadn't followed Mr. Warat,

294
00:27:56,920 --> 00:27:58,120
I might have…

295
00:27:58,880 --> 00:27:59,920
Kluay.

296
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:03,520
Mr. Warat.

297
00:28:04,760 --> 00:28:05,880
You're awake?

298
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,640
Are you hurt?

299
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,280
Please don't disappear like that again.

300
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:21,520
I think you should take the day off today.

301
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:24,120
But I…

302
00:28:25,120 --> 00:28:26,440
Get some rest.

303
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,480
You made the right decision.

304
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:47,600
Dad.

305
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:53,240
But the baby isn't Warat's child.

306
00:28:53,320 --> 00:28:55,560
That's not a problem.

307
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:59,040
You just need to marry Warat first
and register the marriage.

308
00:28:59,120 --> 00:29:01,360
After that,

309
00:29:01,440 --> 00:29:02,800
if he divorces you,

310
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:07,600
half of Vanich's business will be ours.

311
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:11,920
But that's not right, Dad.

312
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:15,400
My dear grandchild,
what perfect timing to be born.

313
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:17,760
But…

314
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:20,720
Det and Kluay…

315
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:23,320
That's not a problem either.

316
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:33,920
Have you told Kluay the truth yet?

317
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,960
- Good. I'll tell her myself.
- Oh?

318
00:29:37,040 --> 00:29:38,920
Why did you treat Ms. Kluay like that?

319
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:41,960
Because it was the best way.

320
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:46,280
What do you mean the best way?

321
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:58,520
Last night,
I think I heard Ms. Ampha's voice.

322
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:05,040
Did you realize what happened last night?

323
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:11,120
It felt like I followed Mr. Warat's voice,

324
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:13,600
but when you got upstairs,
there was nothing.

325
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:19,240
And then I dreamed
of Ms. Ampha holding Waree again.

326
00:30:21,880 --> 00:30:23,240
What's wrong, sweetheart?

327
00:30:23,320 --> 00:30:26,760
What? Are you hungry?

328
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,280
What's wrong?

329
00:30:29,840 --> 00:30:32,280
Did you get scared
because you woke up and didn't see me?

330
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:37,840
Don't be afraid. I'm right here.

331
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:42,160
I promise I'll always stay with you.

332
00:30:42,880 --> 00:30:46,720
<i>Whenever you cry,</i>
<i>I'll come to you right away.</i>

333
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:50,240
What is Ms. Ampha trying to tell me?

334
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:00,600
Ms. Ampha

335
00:31:01,120 --> 00:31:05,800
might have something important
to communicate with you.

336
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:15,360
Then why won't she just tell me
where to find Waree?

337
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:32,240
I've rechecked all the documents
Ms. Kluay compiled.

338
00:31:32,320 --> 00:31:34,760
- Mr. Arnon, what is this?
- Yes.

339
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:38,480
Mrs. Wanee announced this
while you were gone.

340
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:42,840
Why does Jirasin
have so many shares in the will?

341
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:45,240
Wasn't the original version different?

342
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:49,160
Maybe she wants Jirasin to push you.

343
00:31:49,880 --> 00:31:51,160
Oh, Grandma…

344
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:54,560
Wait, what documents
did you say you checked?

345
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:56,280
Ms. Kluay compiled it.

346
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:59,200
All of Jirasin's past transactions.

347
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:00,120
Can you summarize?

348
00:32:01,080 --> 00:32:04,400
In short, just like we thought.

349
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:08,200
Jirasin has been corrupt all along.
He only stopped a few months ago.

350
00:32:08,880 --> 00:32:11,520
He's bad at work and corrupt,

351
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:14,640
yet Grandma still keeps him.
I don't get it.

352
00:32:14,720 --> 00:32:17,440
She must have her reasons.

353
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:25,320
Sin, what is it? Just say it.

354
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:29,640
I have evidence that someone is trying to

355
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,320
make Mr. Warat and me
turn against each other.

356
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:33,080
Where's the evidence?

357
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:34,680
Here it is, Mom.

358
00:32:38,320 --> 00:32:39,360
Here.

359
00:32:39,440 --> 00:32:40,680
What is this?

360
00:32:40,760 --> 00:32:43,520
These are transactions
between me and Vanich Mall.

361
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:46,160
Then why are there two versions?

362
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:47,280
Someone forged them.

363
00:32:49,360 --> 00:32:50,840
Who would dare do this?

364
00:32:52,040 --> 00:32:53,240
<i>Yes, Mr. Sin?</i>

365
00:32:53,320 --> 00:32:55,720
- Hold on.
- Yes?

366
00:32:58,000 --> 00:32:58,960
Yes, Mr. Sin. Alright.

367
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:00,960
Print out the original version too.

368
00:33:01,040 --> 00:33:02,880
- Okay.
- If it's edited,

369
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:06,160
can anyone trace that we modified it?

370
00:33:06,240 --> 00:33:08,800
No way. I locked everything down.

371
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:11,200
And if we compare printed copies?

372
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:14,200
There are no official printouts.

373
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:17,400
They're gone, no way to find them.

374
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:20,560
Here, Mom.
They altered all my transactions.

375
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:24,240
Based on the first set, it makes me
look completely guilty of embezzlement.

376
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:27,280
I know you wouldn't do that.

377
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:29,480
- I know you understand, but--
- Grandma.

378
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:34,760
It's good you're here.
Now we can clear things up.

379
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:37,560
Great. Let's end this misunderstanding.

380
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:39,800
This time, we'll understand correctly.

381
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:44,120
For the past four years,

382
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:48,280
he's been consistently corrupt.

383
00:33:48,880 --> 00:33:50,560
Do you have anything to explain, Sin?

384
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:53,320
Someone's trying to make us
misunderstand each other.

385
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:54,600
What are you talking about?

386
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:57,640
Someone hacked the system
and created fake documents.

387
00:33:57,720 --> 00:34:00,960
What you received
were forged files meant to mislead you.

388
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:05,040
Jirasin, with evidence this clear,

389
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:08,280
you're still making excuses? Enough.

390
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:11,120
Mr. Warat, do you realize
how much our conflict

391
00:34:11,199 --> 00:34:12,840
benefits our competitors?

392
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:18,360
So many big companies
fall over things like this.

393
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:20,239
Grandma, don't listen to him.
I have a witness.

394
00:34:21,080 --> 00:34:22,040
Where?

395
00:34:22,120 --> 00:34:23,360
Our company accountant.

396
00:34:23,440 --> 00:34:24,880
- She's gone.
- Gone where?

397
00:34:24,960 --> 00:34:27,520
She worked for our competitor.
When I caught her,

398
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:28,560
she left.

399
00:34:30,159 --> 00:34:33,440
Mr. Warat, I understand you don't like me

400
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:34,960
for whatever reason.

401
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:38,400
But I want you to know
that I would never steal from Mrs. Wanee.

402
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:41,120
Not even a single baht.

403
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:45,120
As for the forged documents,
I ask for fairness.

404
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:50,600
The data you received
doesn't match the real system.

405
00:34:50,679 --> 00:34:53,239
If you want to verify that,

406
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:54,920
you can check the latest transactions.

407
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:57,800
They'll match this file exactly.

408
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:09,280
Let's just consider this
a fresh start for Vanich.

409
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:11,200
No, Grandma. Never.

410
00:35:11,280 --> 00:35:17,960
Come on, Warat.
You two should stay united.

411
00:35:18,040 --> 00:35:19,200
Most importantly,

412
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:22,320
you still have a long road
working together.

413
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:51,160
- Yes, Mr. Rut?
<i>- Anong,</i>

414
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:54,680
<i>I hear you're back</i>
<i>from the recovery resort.</i>

415
00:35:57,520 --> 00:35:59,960
I'm better now.

416
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,560
And you?

417
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:06,560
What did the doctor say?

418
00:36:06,640 --> 00:36:08,040
<i>Warat knows now.</i>

419
00:36:12,160 --> 00:36:14,640
How did he react?

420
00:36:15,520 --> 00:36:17,480
<i>Not well.</i>

421
00:36:21,440 --> 00:36:23,040
It's okay.

422
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:25,800
These things take time.

423
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:29,720
<i>Thank you, Anong.</i>

424
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:35,360
Do you know?

425
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:37,920
Mr. Warat

426
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:41,400
is now the owner of Vanich,
just as you wanted.

427
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:44,160
<i>That's great.</i>

428
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:13,680
<i>- Kluay.</i>
- Yes?

429
00:37:13,760 --> 00:37:15,320
I broke up with Ameena.

430
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:19,840
How? Weren't you planning to get married?

431
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:22,000
Are you free today?

432
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:25,440
Can we meet?

433
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:27,680
I need your advice.

434
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:34,520
And whose child is Ameena carrying?

435
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:43,360
<i>To manage people,</i>

436
00:37:43,440 --> 00:37:45,960
<i>you don't need to say everything you know.</i>

437
00:37:46,040 --> 00:37:46,880
NEXT EPISODE

438
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:50,640
What matters
is knowing the right moment to say it.

439
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:54,400
Jirasin shouldn't be
holding Vanich shares.

440
00:37:55,880 --> 00:37:56,880
What do you think?

441
00:37:56,960 --> 00:37:59,040
Jirasin shouldn't be
holding any shares at all.

442
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:02,920
Next, we need to make sure the new CEO

443
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:04,520
goes to inspect the site.

444
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,600
What do you want from me, Arnon?

445
00:38:08,480 --> 00:38:10,760
- I just…
- If you love her,

446
00:38:10,840 --> 00:38:12,440
go with her.

447
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:17,120
If the child in her womb
really is Warat's,

448
00:38:17,200 --> 00:38:20,480
we are willing
to take full responsibility.

449
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:24,280
The baby is Warat's.

450
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:28,960
I believe in my partner.

451
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,480
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
